# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1882-louisville-eclipse-season] The **1882 Louisville Eclipse season** was the first season as a Major League club for the franchise.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1882-louisville-eclipse-season] The team, which had played for several years as a semi-pro team, joined the new American Association league.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1882-louisville-eclipse-season] They finished the season with a 42–38 record, good for third place.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1883-louisville-eclipse-season] The **1883 Louisville Eclipse season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1883-louisville-eclipse-season] The team finished with a 52–45 record, fifth place in the American Association.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1884-louisville-eclipse-season] The **1884 Louisville Eclipse season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1884-louisville-eclipse-season] The team finished with a 68–40 record, third place in the American Association.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1884-louisville-eclipse-season] There has been some debate over whom the manager of this club was, with some sources listing the club's starting second baseman, Joe Gerhardt, as manager for at least part of the year, with others crediting team official Mike Walsh with either all or part of the year.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1884-louisville-eclipse-season] Guy Hecker started 75 games for the Eclipse in 1884 and won the American Association Pitching Triple Crown by leading the league in wins, with 52, strikeouts, with 385, and earned run average with 1.80.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1885-louisville-colonels-season] The **1885 Louisville Colonels season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1885-louisville-colonels-season] The team (formerly the Louisville Eclipse) finished with a 53–59 record, tied for fifth place in the American Association.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1886-boston-beaneaters-season] The **1886 Boston Beaneaters season** was the 16th season of the franchise.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1886-brooklyn-grays-season] The **1886 Brooklyn Grays season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1886-brooklyn-grays-season] The team finished the season in third place with a record of 76–61 (their first winning season), 16 games behind the St.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1886-louisville-colonels-season] The **1886 Louisville Colonels season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1886-louisville-colonels-season/1886-louisville-colonels-season] The team finished with a 66–70 record, fourth place in the American Association.
